stories.text:
I have tried to live alone on many instances ranging from 1 to 4 months. But each time anxiety have grappled me from the neck.

It's simply not possible for me to live without constant human interaction.

Now, I want to know if that's possible at all in a healthy way? If so please share your wisdom.
stories.title: Ask HN: How to Live Alone

stories.text:
As per the title I'd like to discuss which type of markets reward the analysis of an underlying asset/event.

Meaning that there is a resolution and you don't need other people to move the market in your favor.

What I came up with is sports betting on events happening within one month, betting on weather events as verified by NOAA weather stations (etc. rain, snow, wind, temperature)
stories.title: Ask HN: Markets in which you aren't reliant on others' opinons to make money?
